&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission Summary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate RVA Instructor plays a critical role in enabling safe, compliant, and scalable autonomous vehicle operations by developing and delivering training programs that prepare Remote Vehicle Assistance (RVA) personnel to support autonomous driving systems. Reporting to the RVA Supervisor, this role serves as a subject matter expert responsible for onboarding, certifying, and continuously developing remote operations personnel through classroom instruction, simulation exercises, and operational coaching. The Associate RVA Instructor partners cross-functionally with Operations, Systems Engineering, Vehicle Integration Engineering, and Learning &amp;amp; Development teams to translate technical system changes into effective training content and operational procedures. By applying technical expertise, instructional excellence, and operational judgment, this role ensures agents are prepared to safely manage routine, non-routine, and complex remote vehicle assistance scenarios while supporting research and development activities, commercialization initiatives, and continuous improvement efforts that advance Motional&#39;s driverless future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
