&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Associate Vehicle Test Specialists support the business by working with Operations, Testing, Autonomy, Mapping, and System and Vehicle Integration Engineers to execute in-vehicle tests, refine test and verification plans, identify and resolve issues, and provide test results. You will communicate between teams and help with improving vehicle testing outcomes. We expect you to hold safety at the highest level while operating, testing, and maintaining our Autonomous Vehicle Fleet (AVs), have strong attention to detail, outstanding verbal and written communication practices, and embrace our core values as a member of the Motional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will focus on safely driving our vehicles, executing in-vehicle tests,&amp;nbsp; reporting test results, coaching new team members on operations processes and procedures, and improving overall testing efficiency by identifying gaps and recommending process refinements. While efficiency is crucial, nothing comes before safety, and the Associate Vehicle Test Specialist is a key team member in upholding this responsibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate prototype-level Autonomous Vehicles on both defined and undefined routes, including a variety of geographic and environmental conditions, including closed course and public road testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate in-vehicle data recording computers, including start/stop recording, data annotations, and debugging when issues arise and coach new team members on the processes and procedures. Provide feedback to engineering teams gathered from testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize JIRA/Confluence software to execute testing tickets and document historical data findings to a global audience and coach new team members on the processes and procedures.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work in a team environment and drive with another person. Maintain cooperative behavior towards fellow team members, including peers, engineers, and members or management and leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to provide quality ride service for passengers when applicable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to read and understand highway, street signs, and all traffic signals in a site-specific location&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains current knowledge and compliance with site-specific traffic laws and regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to communicate proficiently in English (written and spoken) to be able to communicate with public safety officers if necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains current knowledge and adherence to all Motional operating best practices, policies, procedures, and directives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arrives to work on time, prepared with all valid driving credentials and employee ID badge on their person at all time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs pre-trip and post-trip inspection of the Autonomous Vehicle and coaches new team members on the processes and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completes accident and incident reports- as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Control and manage emergencies according to company procedures and coach new team members on the processes and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare, review, revise, and maintain technical documents for standard operating procedures (SOPs), including system/vehicle operations, system/vehicle testing, and user documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support global mapping efforts by collecting mapping data on predefined routes, verifying map changes, and other routing mapping tasks&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be an SME and assist with training current/new hire testing operators, including closed-course/public road facilitation in autonomous and manual methods of driving in addition to computer-based training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support operations metrics tracking and data input

