&lt;h4&gt;Motional’s Las Vegas office is located less than 10 miles from the Las Vegas strip at 730 E Pilot Road and is home to one of the largest fleets of self-driving vehicles. The city’s grid system of roads and being one of America’s “smart cities” allows for extensive research and development testing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mission Summary:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Autonomous Vehicle (AV) Test Engineering team is responsible for validating the safety, functionality, and performance of self-driving technology through rigorous, system-level testing. As a Systems Test Engineer, you will play a hands-on role in the end-to-end verification of AV features—spanning perception, planning, and control—across virtual, closed-course, and public road environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a versatile engineer to contribute to test strategy, scenario creation, and infrastructure development. Whether your expertise lies in Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL), synthetic simulation, or physical track testing, you will help translate engineering requirements into comprehensive test plans and measurable outcomes. Your efforts will support iterative development, fault injection analysis, and safety-critical system evaluation to ensure every release meets the highest standards for quality and reliability.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test Design &amp;amp; Execution: Design and execute test campaigns for self-driving features (perception, planning, and control) across virtual, synthetic, and physical environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multi-Modal Validation: Leverage Software-in-the-Loop (SIL), Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL), and scenario-based simulation platforms (e.g., Applied Intuition) for feature validation and regression testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simulation &amp;amp; Resimulation: Create synthetic and log-replay scenarios to support root-cause analysis and large-scale release validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track &amp;amp; Systems Integration: Perform mechatronic and systems integration testing, including closed-course test track validation and on-vehicle environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automation: Develop and maintain detailed test plans and automation scripts using Python and Bash/Shell.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Analysis: Analyze logs and data to assess system behavior and conduct root-cause investigations, collaborating cross-functionally with perception, planning, hardware, and safety teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hardware Debugging: Conduct fault injection and low-level control testing using tools like CANalyzer or CANoe for subsystems such as drive-by-wire (DBW), braking, and steering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compliance: Ensure testing practices align with industry standards such as ISO 26262, ISO 21448 (SOTIF), and ISO 9001.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration: Document procedures and technical findings using tools like Confluence, Jira, and GitLab to ensure traceability.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: Bachelor’s degree or higher in Engineering, Robotics, ECE, Computer Science, or a relevant technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 2+ years in software QA, systems testing, or mechatronic system validation, preferably within ADAS or autonomous systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Skills:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Linux and programming/scripting languages such as Python, C++, or Bash/Shell.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing and developing comprehensive test cases and test plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Domain Expertise (One or more of the following):&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Virtual/Simulation: Proficiency with AV simulation platforms (e.g., Applied Intuition, IPG Carmaker, NVIDIA DRIVE Sim).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HIL/Hardware: Hands-on experience with Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL) environments and

